&lt;p&gt;Experienced Band 5 Critical Care Nurses&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Royal Free and Barnet Critical Care teams are looking to recruit experienced Band 5 Nurses who have significant Critical Care experience. Successful candidates will undertake our Band 5 to 6 development programme.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Successful candidates will undertake the:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Royal Free London NHS Trust “Adult Intensive Care Course” which is fully accredited with the University of Greenwich ( 30 level 6 credits) and the Intermediate Life Support Course&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Band 5 to 6 transition programme*&lt;br /&gt;* Transition to Band 6 only once agreed competences are met&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Opportunity to rotate between both ICU’s&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Royal Free Intensive Care Unit comprises of 34, level 3 beds, and admits in excess of 1700 patients per year. Specialties at the RFH include Hepato-biliary services, an established liver transplantation programme, haematology, complex vascular surgery, colorectal surgery, plastic surgery and renal services.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Barnet Intensive Care unit comprises of 23 bed, 10 level 2 and 13 level 3. The unit admits in excess of 600 patients per year. Specialties include general medical and surgical patients, patients requiring renal replacement therapies, spinal, plastic and complex lower GI.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As you can see we are committed to developing and supporting a modern career framework for our Nurses and you will be supported every step of your critical care career pathway by our Clinical Practice education team and senior team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Please note that these vacancies may close prior to the advertised closing date, subject to the high number of applicants anticipated. The assessment day involves a drug calculations and scenario test followed by face to face interviews should you pass the test.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due to social distancing and Covid 19 pressures you will be contacted if successful in shortlisting with further details regarding test (if required) and interview. We will use Microsoft Teams to conduct testing and interviews. Due to challenging times we are experiencing you may be asked to go to different departments and work under difficult circumstances.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We support flexible working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
